<div class="tip-card"><strong>Special: Furnace Core recipe!</strong><br>To craft a Furnace Core, the workbench itself goes into the center slot of the crafting grid — and gets consumed!
<ul style="margin:6px 0 0 0">
  <li><strong>Stone Furnace Core:</strong> 8× Cobblestone + <em>Copper</em> or <em>Silver Workbench</em> (center)</li>
  <li><strong>Obsidian Furnace Core:</strong> 8× Obsidian + <em>Gold</em> or <em>Iron Workbench</em> (center)</li>
  <li><strong>Netherrack Furnace Core:</strong> 8× Netherrack + <em>Mithril</em> or <em>Adamantium Workbench</em> (center)</li>
</ul></div>

<p>Every workbench also has an <strong>Auto</strong> variant (upgradeable with PCB)!</p>
<div class="tip-card">🔌 <strong>PCB:</strong> hold it in hand and <strong>right-click a workbench</strong> to turn it into its auto variant. According to the local mod-doc, PCBs have a <strong>50%</strong> chest chance in the trophy chests of <strong>underground ancient skeleton spawner</strong> ruins.</div>

<h3>Maximum Item Quality by Material</h3>
<p>Each material can only craft items up to a certain quality tier. Rarer materials gradually unlock higher quality tiers, up to legendary quality.</p>
